<br>
Raid Structure<br>
===========<br>
Raid Leaders = Tempestade & Colubridae<br>
Lotto Captain = Tempestade<br>
Puller = Kikulle<br>
Secondary Pullers = Sollron & Kerekian<br>
Main Assist = Colubridae<br>
Secondary Assist - Nillis<br>
Main Mezer = Tashia (also speed)<br>
Secondary Mezer = Lillypaws (also C2)<br>
Primary Rezer = Huffty<br>
Secondary Rezer = Feydis<br>
Scouts (for break) = Sollron, Kikulle, Kerekian<br>
Twitchers (clerics and chanters have priority) = Spus, Elmira, Oosz<br>
Snares = Rjak & Readd<br>
<br>
The BEST Fear guide out there was written by Tashia for the Xegony Alliance. Even if you've been to Fear 1000 times, PLEASE read it. It can be found at: <br>
http://www.xegonyalliance.com/guides/pofguide.html<br>
<br>
Col will talk about strategy. Here are some hints about lottos:<br>
<br>
1. If your group got the kill, make sure you don't check the mob if it drops your class armor. Ask someone else to do it.<br>
2. Report drops in TELLS to the lotto captain. Why in tells? Because if you do a /ooc, the lotto captain gets spammed with questions and tells before they have the chance to get organized.<br>
3. As soon as the lotto captain shouts a drop, give him/her a TELL if you want in. Pay attention to see if you're included and the lotto captain didn't miss your tell (it does happen!). <br>
4. READ the DoK lotto rules at www.keldar.com. By coming to the raid you're accepting those rules.<br>
5. Get familiar with the drops for your class and what mobs drop them. But for God's sake, don't pester the pullers about what they are pulling. They will bring what they can.<br>
<br>
***HINT*** Tanks MUST bind in Oggok, good race or not. I will have a mule parked there to hand sow potions and invis potions to people who die during the break. Casters and healers MUST bind at the portal.<br>
